Patients will be offered at least three high street chemist appointments for up to 12 weeks as well as supplies of medicines such as patches. Marking National No Smoking Day today, health chiefs said all pharmacists can now offer the service after a pilot scheme in Greater Manchester. Dr Bola Owolabi, of NHS England, said: "Leaving hospital is a good incentive for people to quit smoking - and NHS pharmacies will help them stub out the dangerous habit once and for all." More than half a million NHS hospital admissions a year are blamed on smoking.